snippet: Mustafa Abdel-Jalil, head of the Transitional National Council, said he could not use force against tribal leaders who are moving toward semiautonomy for their oil-rich eastern region.
abstract: Mustafa Abdel-Jalil, head of the Transitional National Council in Libya, says he cannot use force against tribal leaders who are moving toward semiautonomy for their oil-rich eastern region; says the council does not have enough forces to confront them.
lead_paragraph: Mustafa Abdel-Jalil, head of the Transitional National Council, said he could not use force against tribal leaders who are moving toward semiautonomy for their oil-rich eastern region.

headline.main: Libya: Leader Says Force Against Tribal Leaders Isn’t Possible
